reviews.text: Dinner was great! The chicken tenders were crispy on the outside and juicy on the inside. I tried the OxSauce, Kickin-Sauce, and honey mustard. OxSauce is obviously meant to compare to other special sauces elsewhere and it did not disappoint. The cinnamon pretzels and icing dip were also good!

We stopped by after moving our son in. The owner was so friendly and welcoming. You can tell he really loves this place and takes great pride in it. The food was fantastic. The chicken was juicy and flavorful. The Mac n cheese was delicious. Now let's talk about the waffle fries. They, hands down were so good. They had the perfect amount of seasoning and cooked perfectly. It was also so great to grab a draft beer as well. We can't wait to go back.

I‚Äôve been waiting for this place to open for a long time and it did not disappoint!

I ended up getting the three piece combo, or ‚ÄúThe Freshman‚Äù with a side of Mac and Cheese. The chicken was perfect, and I enjoyed the fries too!

Service-wise it was cool to see the owners both involved in making the food and checking on everyone.

Overall plan on going here as much as I can and the late night hours will be great for after the bars close.

First time visiting. We were greeted immediately by the general manager who gave a quick run down of the menu. You can tell this guy loved his job, was super passionate and excited about this place. And I see why. The chicken was amazing. It was tender, juicy, hot, flavorful. Generous sauce portions. They also have a bar. I‚Äôm with their own ipa and lager too. We will be back over and over. We noticed an outside eating area but it was really hot today. We will def be checking that out when it‚Äôs not so hot.

Traveled to Oxford from southern Ohio to visit my Grandson. He is a sophomore at Miami University. Two of his roommates joined us. The food was amazing! The boys had never been to OxVegas chicken before, They will be coming back !

detailedReviews.text: OxVegas chicken is Oxfords newest chicken spot. To start out with the negatives, this place is always incredibly dirty when it‚Äôs busy. I would cut them some slack if they weren‚Äôt so stingy about giving an extra sauce but they WILL NOT give u an extra ranch or any sauce if you ask. Customer service is everything and if you can‚Äôt perform in food quality maybe shine with your costumer service. detailedReviews.author: Chuk Lee
detailedReviews.text: I so badly wanted to give this place a good review.  For a while I couldn't even go because they did not accept cash.  Fortunately, they reversed that.  Shortly after that, I came to try it out, but was told they ran out of chicken.  A few months later, I finally got to try it out, They had a kiosk order system, however, after I had made out my order on there it asked me if I wanted to pay by card, there is no option for cash on the kiosk. There was a note to see an employee if you were paying cash, I thought that would get my order committed after having placed it in the kiosk. We had to go over to the bar to place the order, girl behind the bar was very nice, but there was a swarm of gnats going on. Got the "junior" meal, It was out very quickly. There was a hamburger bun top with garlic butter on it.  That seemed a little weird, this would be much better with Texas toast.  The 'kickin' sauce was just a Tabasco, the barbecue seemed out of a bottle.  The chicken by itself was good. The windows were desperately in need of a clean, I would highly recommend they get a professional window cleaner. Almost impossible to enjoy the meal because of the flies. If the owners read this review, hire professional window cleaners.  Take some aggressive action to mitigate the flying insects.  Fix your point of sale to accept cash on pickup, so you don't waste people's time.  Keep your tables clean. Was very impressed when the girl who took our order asked for my review.

detailedReviews.text: Simply put, fresher version of Canes & Zaxby‚Äôs. Tenders hand breaded after ordering!

detailedReviews.author: Willow Dunning
detailedReviews.text: I guess I wouldn't have such a problem if it didn't feel like they were cheaping out at every turn. Charging $2.49 for an 8oz cup, the chicken is the size of chicken nuggets at McDonald's (and worse taste), and charging extra for more than one sauce. This whole place just screamed cheap and low quality but then charged you as if it was a nice restaurant.

detailedReviews.author: Paul Arel
detailedReviews.text: Great new Uptown Oxford chicken place owned and operated by 2 Miami alum. Limited menu of chicken tenders and sides, but hey, the chicken IS righteously delicious!! Very tender (no pun intended...) and juicy, with a nice, crisp breading. Like the option of having a beer or cocktail with my tenders too!  I'd prefer my Texas toast to be toasted on both sides, but other places do it this way too, so...  Looking forward to trying more homemade sauce flavors as they're getting their feet wet and start to make their own way. Highly recommended!!

detailedReviews.text: A solid chicken option here in Oxford! We enjoyed the sophomore combo at the summer promotional event today. It was especially a hit with our toddlers. The staff was welcoming and hard-working with the huge crowd. The food came out quickly and was piping hot and delicious! The portions were VERY generous. We would gladly eat here again!

detailedReviews.text: My bride to be and I, along with he maid of honor came to look at a wedding venue, after the appointment we decided to go to Oxford for lunch. We came across this wonderful establishment, the manager was amazing and let us take a picture with the chickens in the car and came in to a very pleasant and happy environment. This place would get a 10/10 if I could put it on here. Highly recommended

detailedReviews.author: Rhett Johnson
detailedReviews.text: Ordered the Sophomore and it came out in decent time. Their special sauce tastes like ketchup and mayo. The food was good but the drinks were ridiculously expensive. 2 shots were $17.02. We told the staff we weren‚Äôt okay with paying that and they were understanding and refunded us. 10/10 staff 7/10 food 10/10 atmosphere 3/10 prices.

detailedReviews.author: Corben Shoemaker
detailedReviews.text: Oxvegas is truly amazing! The hospitality goes all the way from the cashier to the owner. Jackson Trester went above and beyond to make sure his customers were taken care of and had the best dining experience possible. The Oxvegas beer was a staple and the patio seating capped off a spring evening perfectly.

detailedReviews.author: Ryan Wiesman
detailedReviews.text: Local business, delicious Chicken, fast friendly service, incredible vibes. 10/10.

detailedReviews.author: Brooke Dorrmann
detailedReviews.text: literally the best chicken i‚Äôve ever had, i‚Äôve heard a lot of hype and yall totally stand up to it!! the oxvegas sauce is sooooooooooo good

detailedReviews.author: Joe Bateman
detailedReviews.text: Very impressed! I honestly think this is better than Caines. The chicken was super tender and juicy. The outer coating had that perfect crunch but also not too hard. Super flavorful! The fries had great flavoring also. Just wish they were a tad bit more crisp. The oxvegas sauce was sweet and zesty. Not too goopy but also not overly thin. My only complaint about the food is the bread. It‚Äôs just a toasted piece of bread. No flavor. I wish it had a garlic flavor. Super fast! Employees were very nice and it has a very welcoming atmosphere! I will definitely be back!

detailedReviews.author: Aleks Cheris
detailedReviews.text: The atmosphere is unbelievable! The bar is just perfect for the restaurant! Walking into oxvegas I just feel like it‚Äôs a second home to me! Currently about to go eat there once again. The sauce is amazing, and nothing will stop me from going again!

detailedReviews.author: Kyle Innis

detailedReviews.author: Haley Mobley

detailedReviews.text: Their chicken tenders are small enough that I'd call them chicken NUGGETS. For the amount that they charge for this food, I feel a little stolen from after buying the Senior combo for 8 tenders and getting the equivalent of about four tenders from any other restaurant. The convenience of having a nice chicken place in Oxford is great...but they need to improve the consistency of the meals that they provide.

detailedReviews.text: I got really bad food poisoning. I noticed my chicken tasted a bit off and now I‚Äôm extremely sick. I have also now heard of 4 other people getting food poisoning from here too.
